<div id="sub"><a id="5"></a>text formatting in CSS3</div>
<div id="div3">this will help you when the word is too long to and break it when it when it goes out of the box</div>
<pre>
word-wrap:break-word;
text-shadow:2px 2px 4px pink;
/*there is a property "word-break:break-all"
this will break at any point line
when width end even in middle of any word*/
</pre>
<div id="div4">the overflow is can be seen & the height don't increase. 
</div>
<pre>
/*if you write hidden instead of visible 
the text outside the box will hidden*/
/*also you can add "text-overfloe:ellipsis" 
this will put ".." when the text overflow*/
overflow:visible;
white-space:nowrap;
</pre>
<div id="sub"><a id="6"></a>transition effect</div>
<div id="div5">..hover here..</div>
<pre>
#div5{
width:200px;
padding:4px;
background:#66ccff;
transition: background 4s linear,width 2s ease-in,
border-radius 4s;
/*in transition write the attributes define in hover*/
/*also with time & way like linear and ease-in*/
}
#div5:hover{
background:#aa00ff;
border-radius:20px;
border:4px solid white;
width:250px;
box-shadow: 0 4px 8px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2),
0 6px 20px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.19);
}
</pre>
<div id="sub"><a id="7"></a>animation</div>
<div id="div6"></div>
<pre>
#div6{
width:200px;
height:200px;
padding:4px;
background:white;
box-shadow: 0 4px 8px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2),
0 6px 20px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.19);
animation-name:anime /*time can be defined here also*/;
animation-duration:8s;
animation-timing-function:linear;
/*remove breaks in your animation*/
/*other option can be ease-in, ease-out*/
animation-iteration-count:infinite;
/*no. of time the animayion repeat*/
}
/*for animation you have to create keyframes*/
@keyframes anime{
0%{background:white;200px;border-radius:0px;}
20%{background:#ffff66;border-radius:50px;}
40%{background:#66ff66;border-radius:100px;}
60%{background:	#6666ff;border-radius:100px;}
80%{background:#ff6666;border-radius:50px;}
100%{background:white;border-radius:0px;}
/*in place of % you can directly use from{} & to{}*/
}
</pre>
<div id="sub"><a id="8"></a>some filter that you can apply on an image</div>
<div id="div7">
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" >
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:grayscale(100%);">
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:contrast(200%);"><br>
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:invert(100%);">
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:opacity(60%);">
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:saturate(1000%);"><br>
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:blur(1px);">
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:sepia(100%);">
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:hue-rotate(45deg);"><br>
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:brightness(150%);">
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:brightness(50%);">
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif" style="filter:blur(1px) saturate(1000%) contrast(200%);">
</div>
<pre>
/*inserting an image*/

/*original image1*/
&lt;img src="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/img_colormap.gif">

/*filters*/

/*image2*/
filter:grayscale(100%);
/*image3*/
filter:contrast(200%);
/*image4*/
filter:invert(100%);
/*image5*/
filter:opacity(60%);
/*image6*/
filter:saturate(1000%);
/*image7*/
filter:blur(1px);
/*image8*/
filter:sepia(100%);
/*image9*/
filter:hue-rotate(45deg);
/*image10*/
filter:brightness(150%);
/*image11*/
filter:brightness(50%);
/*you can apply multiple filter together*/
/*image12*/
filter:blur(1px) saturate(1000%) contrast(200%);
/*if the filter don't work use -webkit-*/
/*eg -webkit-filter:blur(1px);*/
/*add this in your style*/
/*it may vary for different bowser*/
</pre>
